Dialogue: 0.0:00:02.45.0:00:03.86.Default..0.0.0..Now kids. when\NAunt Robin was a teenager.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:03.88.0:00:07.94.Default..0.0.0..she was. well.\Na Canadian pop star.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:08.00.0:00:10.89.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}But by 2008. she was\Nan entirely different person.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:00:15.68.0:00:19.90.Default..0.0.0..Coming up next. is your\Nbaby trying to kill you?
Dialogue: 0.0:00:19.97.0:00:22.84.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}Which made the events\Nof that week all the more surprising.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:00:22.87.0:00:25.32.Default..0.0.0..So I go in this morning\Nand it's freezing.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:25.39.0:00:27.95.Default..0.0.0..so I walk over there. and I\Ndon't know why I'm still talking.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:28.02.0:00:30.42.Default..0.0.0..because. clearly. we're all\Nasking the same question.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:30.49.0:00:32.96.Default..0.0.0..what in God's creation is\Ngoing on with Robin's breasts?
Dialogue: 0.0:00:33.03.0:00:35.75.Default..0.0.0..I know. right?\NIsn't it amazing?
Dialogue: 0.0:00:35.81.0:00:37.88.Default..0.0.0..I spent half an hour\Nmaking this happen.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:37.90.0:00:39.74.Default..0.0.0..There's tape in there.\Ncotton balls.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:39.77.0:00:41.85.Default..0.0.0..half of a Nerf football.\Nbut it works. right?
Dialogue: 0.0:00:41.87.0:00:43.75.Default..0.0.0..Totally.\NWhat's the occasion?
Dialogue: 0.0:00:43.82.0:00:46.99.Default..0.0.0..An old friend from Canada is in\Ntown and I'm meeting him for a drink.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:47.06.0:00:49.44.Default..0.0.0..Ooh! Somebody you went\Nto Degrassi with?
Dialogue: 0.0:00:49.51.0:00:53.25.Default..0.0.0..No. Actually. he was\Nmy first boyfriend.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:53.32.0:00:57.55.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}Simon. I thought\Nhe was the coolest guy ever.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:00:57.62.0:01:00.99.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}He smelled like Drakkar. He\Ncould ollie on a skateboard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:01:01.06.0:01:06.09.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}And he had the most amazing\Ncollection of Hard Rock Cafe T-shirts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:01:06.16.0:01:09.76.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}We spent the\Nwhole summer madly in love.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:01:09.78.0:01:13.35.Default..0.0.0..Tell me more. Tell me more.\NLike. did he have a car?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:15.05.0:01:19.62.Default..0.0.0..So. is he the guy who... How\Nshall I say this like a gentleman?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:19.69.0:01:21.45.Default..0.0.0..Robin. did he take\Nyour maple leaf?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:22.71.0:01:24.46.Default..0.0.0..No. it wasn't like that.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:24.48.0:01:27.66.Default..0.0.0..Sounds to me like he gave\Nyou your first {\i1}O Canada{\i0} face.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:29.15.0:01:31.35.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}This went on\Nfor a really long time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:01:31.37.0:01:33.45.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}Some of the jokes were elegant\Nand well crafted...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:01:33.47.0:01:35.05.Default..0.0.0..Wait. wait.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:35.12.0:01:38.06.Default..0.0.0..Did he break up with you and\Ntell you he's just not that Inuit?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:39.96.0:01:42.02.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}Others\Nwere crude. and ill-formed...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:01:42.05.0:01:45.58.Default..0.0.0..Something about fur trapping.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:45.65.0:01:48.11.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}And others were\Nobvious. but needed to be said...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:01:48.14.0:01:49.85.Default..0.0.0..Did you ride his Zamboni?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:49.87.0:01:51.52.Default..0.0.0..Oh!
Dialogue: 0.0:01:52.71.0:01:54.82.Default..0.0.0..Wait. wait. wait.\NDid he...
Dialogue: 0.0:01:56.76.0:01:58.11.Default..0.0.0..I think I'm out.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:58.18.0:02:00.26.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. I'm also out.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:01.43.0:02:03.65.Default..0.0.0..Okay. now I'm really out.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:03.72.0:02:05.68.Default..0.0.0..Well. I'm sorry. guys.\NIt was all very tame.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:05.70.0:02:07.60.Default..0.0.0..We only dated\Nfor a week and a half.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:07.67.0:02:10.09.Default..0.0.0..What? I thought you said\Nyou were together all summer.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:10.16.0:02:13.41.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. Summer in Canada is\Npretty much the last week of July.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:13.50.0:02:16.70.Default..0.0.0..Anyway. one night. his band\Njust finished playing this gig...
Dialogue: 0.0:02:21.59.0:02:26.59.Default..0.0.0..Oh. my God! Simon.\NThat was such a good show.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:26.66.0:02:29.36.Default..0.0.0..You guys totally rocked out.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:29.43.0:02:31.60.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. I know.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:31.66.0:02:35.77.Default..0.0.0..I figure we're about four or five\Ngigs away from really exploding.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:35.83.0:02:39.29.Default..0.0.0..We're gonna be big. babe. I\Nmean. like Crash Test Dummies big.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:41.36.0:02:42.96.Default..0.0.0..So. that everything?
Dialogue: 0.0:02:43.02.0:02:44.09.Default..0.0.0..Yeah.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:44.16.0:02:45.53.Default..0.0.0..All right.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:46.85.0:02:48.40.Default..0.0.0..Listen. babe...
Dialogue: 0.0:02:49.43.0:02:50.78.Default..0.0.0..It's over.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:52.40.0:02:53.67.Default..0.0.0..What?
Dialogue: 0.0:02:53.74.0:02:56.82.Default..0.0.0..I'm getting back together\Nwith Louise Marsh.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:56.89.0:03:01.01.Default..0.0.0..Louise Marsh? That's a\Nwhore's name if I ever heard one.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:01.08.0:03:04.36.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. why would he want to get\Nback together with Louise Marsh?
Dialogue: 0.0:03:04.88.0:03:06.71.Default..0.0.0..Well. the thing is.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:08.15.0:03:10.30.Default..0.0.0..her folks just put in a pool.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:10.37.0:03:11.86.Default..0.0.0..Oh.\NSo...
Dialogue: 0.0:03:11.89.0:03:17.42.Default..0.0.0..Totally. I get it. Pools are\Ngreat. Swimming's awesome.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:19.01.0:03:21.96.Default..0.0.0..We have a sprinkler.\NRun right through it.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:24.37.0:03:26.07.Default..0.0.0..Well. I should go.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:29.07.0:03:30.60.Default..0.0.0..Babe. wait.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:31.67.0:03:33.47.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. Simon?
Dialogue: 0.0:03:33.54.0:03:35.88.Default..0.0.0..You forgot to load the drum set.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:37.11.0:03:38.13.Default..0.0.0..No!
Dialogue: 0.0:03:38.21.0:03:40.91.Default..0.0.0..Tell me you did not\Nload the drum set.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:40.98.0:03:42.15.Default..0.0.0..I did.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:43.92.0:03:47.04.Default..0.0.0..And now he's coming here? Robin.\Nwhy do you want to see this guy?
Dialogue: 0.0:03:47.11.0:03:51.22.Default..0.0.0..Oh! I know why. You're\Ngonna win. aren't you?
Dialogue: 0.0:03:51.29.0:03:53.55.Default..0.0.0..I have no idea what\Nyou're talking about.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:53.58.0:03:54.91.Default..0.0.0..Yes. you do.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:54.98.0:03:56.12.Default..0.0.0..Whenever you haven't\Nseen someone for a long time.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:56.15.0:03:57.56.Default..0.0.0..no matter how much\Nyou want to deny it.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:57.58.0:04:00.08.Default..0.0.0..there's always a clear\Nwinner and a clear loser.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:00.15.0:04:02.73.Default..0.0.0..Okay. well. since you brought\Nit up. let's add up the points.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:02.76.0:04:05.35.Default..0.0.0..You're starting out with\Ntwo big ones right there.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:05.37.0:04:08.88.Default..0.0.0..Thank you. Okay. So.\NSimon still lives with his mom.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:08.94.0:04:10.14.Default..0.0.0..Point Robin.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:10.21.0:04:11.59.Default..0.0.0..He never became a rock star.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:11.61.0:04:12.81.Default..0.0.0..Point Robin.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:12.88.0:04:15.49.Default..0.0.0..He now works at a water\Nslide park outside of Ottawa.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:15.52.0:04:16.58.Default..0.0.0..Point Simon.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:16.60.0:04:17.72.Default..0.0.0..Wait.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:17.79.0:04:19.83.Default..0.0.0..Do they have a wave pool?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:19.87.0:04:22.91.Default..0.0.0..Point Robin. That's 5-zip.\NThere's no coming back from that.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:22.98.0:04:26.79.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. he's going down. I mean.\Nunless somehow he got hotter.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:28.80.0:04:30.16.Default..0.0.0..There he is.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:30.23.0:04:32.93.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}And sure\Nenough. there was a clear winner{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:04:33.00.0:04:34.67.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}and a clear loser.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:04:38.29.0:04:40.91.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}It just wasn't clear\Nto everybody.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:04:40.98.0:04:42.31.Default..0.0.0..Hey. babe.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:43.20.0:04:44.43.Default..0.0.0..Oh. my God.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:00.91.0:05:03.23.Default..0.0.0..Okay. what the hell\Njust happened?
Dialogue: 0.0:05:03.28.0:05:05.78.Default..0.0.0..Oh. come on. it\Nwasn't so bad. was it?
Dialogue: 0.0:05:07.35.0:05:08.35.Default..0.0.0..Hey. Simon.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:08.42.0:05:10.59.Default..0.0.0..Wow. look at you.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:11.66.0:05:14.27.Default..0.0.0..You got old.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:14.34.0:05:19.43.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. You look great. You\Ngot hotter. like that's possible.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:21.05.0:05:22.52.Default..0.0.0..So...
Dialogue: 0.0:05:22.58.0:05:27.05.Default..0.0.0..Look. I know it didn't go as\Nplanned. but I can't help it.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:27.12.0:05:30.44.Default..0.0.0..I mean. he's still got it.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:30.53.0:05:35.86.Default..0.0.0..Whoa! 4 bucks for a brew?\NWhat a rip. Good thing I'm packing.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:39.50.0:05:41.22.Default..0.0.0..So he's not a snob.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:41.29.0:05:43.77.Default..0.0.0..He's from a different part\Nof Canada. you know?
Dialogue: 0.0:05:43.84.0:05:46.94.Default..0.0.0..The maple leaf flag on the\Nback of the pickup truck?
Dialogue: 0.0:05:47.01.0:05:50.23.Default..0.0.0..He's Red Province.\NHe's from the Deep North.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:50.30.0:05:53.68.Default..0.0.0..And the thing is. we gave\Nyou so many opportunities.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:53.75.0:05:57.60.Default..0.0.0..So. Simon. Robin's a bit of a\Nlocal celebrity here in New York.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:57.69.0:06:00.30.Default..0.0.0..She's the lead anchor\Nat Metro News 1.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:00.37.0:06:01.39.Default..0.0.0..Tell him. Robin.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:01.46.0:06:02.71.Default..0.0.0..No. It's stupid.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:02.77.0:06:06.04.Default..0.0.0..It's not cool.\Nlike Simon's shirt.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:06.11.0:06:10.35.Default..0.0.0..I'm sorry. Simon. Here we are\Nnattering on about our big celebrity.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:10.42.0:06:11.93.Default..0.0.0..What do you do for a living?
Dialogue: 0.0:06:11.95.0:06:15.34.Default..0.0.0..Oh. I work at the Splish\NSplash Ottawa Water Slide Park.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:15.40.0:06:18.71.Default..0.0.0..A water slide park. That sure is\Ndifferent than what Robin does.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:18.77.0:06:22.66.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. it is.\Nbecause I save lives.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:22.73.0:06:26.48.Default..0.0.0..If I'm not sitting in that stool\Nat the top of the slide. going.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:26.55.0:06:32.09.Default..0.0.0.."Go. go. go." people die.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:33.72.0:06:37.01.Default..0.0.0..What. you think it's\Nso easy? You try it.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:37.08.0:06:39.18.Default..0.0.0..Okay.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:39.24.0:06:40.29.Default..0.0.0..Go.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:40.36.0:06:41.84.Default..0.0.0..You didn't put your\Nhand up. kid just died.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:41.86.0:06:42.98.Default..0.0.0..No. I didn't know...
Dialogue: 0.0:06:43.05.0:06:44.44.Default..0.0.0..Another kid just went.\NHe died. too.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:44.47.0:06:45.71.Default..0.0.0..Oh. well. sure. I\Nmean. if I was actually...
Dialogue: 0.0:06:45.73.0:06:47.47.Default..0.0.0..Another kid just went.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:47.54.0:06:49.51.Default..0.0.0..Now you've got a pile-up and Robin's\Ngot something to report on the news.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:49.54.0:06:54.11.Default..0.0.0.."This just in. my friend Ted\Nkilled a bunch of kids today."
Dialogue: 0.0:06:54.18.0:06:56.54.Default..0.0.0..Well. that's cool. You got\Nto pay the bills somehow
Dialogue: 0.0:06:56.61.0:06:58.95.Default..0.0.0..since your whole music thing\Ndidn't really pan out.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:59.01.0:07:00.67.Default..0.0.0..did it? Well. it hasn't\Npanned out yet.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:00.70.0:07:02.01.Default..0.0.0..but the band's still going.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:02.03.0:07:05.27.Default..0.0.0..About four or five gigs\Naway from really exploding.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:05.34.0:07:07.65.Default..0.0.0..The Foreskins are still playing?
Dialogue: 0.0:07:08.36.0:07:10.47.Default..0.0.0..The Foreskins?
Dialogue: 0.0:07:10.54.0:07:12.37.Default..0.0.0..How'd you guys\Ncome up with that name?
Dialogue: 0.0:07:13.75.0:07:17.13.Default..0.0.0..Well. there's four of us.\Nand we play without shirts.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:18.23.0:07:20.05.Default..0.0.0..Babe. seriously.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:20.12.0:07:22.44.Default..0.0.0..I know. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:24.36.0:07:28.83.Default..0.0.0..I know. I'm sorry. But you\Nguys just don't understand.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:28.89.0:07:31.96.Default..0.0.0..The fact that he kept the\Nband going. that's impressive.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:32.03.0:07:34.30.Default..0.0.0..I mean. I gave up\Nmy musical dream.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:34.37.0:07:36.76.Default..0.0.0..Which brings us to the\Nmost important piece
Dialogue: 0.0:07:36.79.0:07:40.07.Default..0.0.0..of information from tonight.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:40.14.0:07:42.22.Default..0.0.0..So. Simon.\Nhow did you guys meet?
Dialogue: 0.0:07:42.29.0:07:43.87.Default..0.0.0..Oh. I was in her video.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:43.94.0:07:46.91.Default..0.0.0..Starred in it is more like it.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:46.98.0:07:48.76.Default..0.0.0..Once you win\NMr. Teen Winnipeg.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:48.78.0:07:52.13.Default..0.0.0..everybody wants a piece\Nof the moneymaker.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:52.20.0:07:55.55.Default..0.0.0..I'm sorry. I've seen {\i1}Let's Go\Nto the Mall{\i0} about 1.000 times.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:55.62.0:07:56.81.Default..0.0.0..and you. sir. are not in it.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:56.84.0:07:58.89.Default..0.0.0..I was in the other one.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:58.96.0:08:00.84.Default..0.0.0..There's another video?
Dialogue: 0.0:08:05.43.0:08:07.13.Default..0.0.0..Robin. seriously.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:07.22.0:08:10.67.Default..0.0.0..just make this easier on\Nyourself and give us the tape.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:10.74.0:08:11.88.Default..0.0.0..No.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:11.95.0:08:14.25.Default..0.0.0..All right.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:14.32.0:08:17.46.Default..0.0.0..You leave me no choice.\NFrom this moment on.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:17.53.0:08:23.03.Default..0.0.0..I will spend every waking\Nminute searching down this tape.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:23.10.0:08:25.40.Default..0.0.0..I will not sleep.\NI will not eat.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:25.47.0:08:28.90.Default..0.0.0..My life will be a living\Nhell of search engines
Dialogue: 0.0:08:28.97.0:08:31.00.Default..0.0.0..and overseas phone calls.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:31.07.0:08:34.36.Default..0.0.0..chasing down something\Nthat possibly can't be found.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:35.51.0:08:37.93.Default..0.0.0..Okay.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:38.00.0:08:42.53.Default..0.0.0..It's just... It was so hard to watch.\NRobin. You're usually so cool.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:42.60.0:08:44.60.Default..0.0.0..I don't know\Nwhat's wrong with me.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:44.62.0:08:48.07.Default..0.0.0..I'm sitting next to Simon.\Nand suddenly I'm 16 again.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:48.14.0:08:49.50.Default..0.0.0..Oh. it's actually\Na common thing.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:49.52.0:08:51.24.Default..0.0.0..When you're around someone\Nfrom your past.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:51.26.0:08:53.91.Default..0.0.0..you kind of revert back to who\Nyou were when you knew them.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:53.98.0:08:55.64.Default..0.0.0..There's not really\Na name for it. though.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:55.66.0:08:56.91.Default..0.0.0..It's called\N"revertigo."
Dialogue: 0.0:08:56.93.0:08:59.20.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. I don't know\Nabout "revertigo."
Dialogue: 0.0:08:59.27.0:09:01.97.Default..0.0.0..You know who gets\Nreally bad revertigo?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:03.44.0:09:06.48.Default..0.0.0..Lily when she's around her\Nhigh school friend. Michelle.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:06.51.0:09:08.54.Default..0.0.0..Michelle? She sounds hot.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:08.61.0:09:11.74.Default..0.0.0..Wait. wait. You don't know\Nabout Lily and Michelle?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:11.81.0:09:13.96.Default..0.0.0..No. What about\NLily and Michelle?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:14.03.0:09:16.98.Default..0.0.0..Oh. my friend. you\Nare in for a treat.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:17.00.0:09:18.38.Default..0.0.0..Hey. Lil?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:18.45.0:09:19.81.Default..0.0.0..You know. I was just thinking.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:19.84.0:09:21.52.Default..0.0.0..we haven't seen your\Nfriend Michelle in a while.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:21.54.0:09:24.46.Default..0.0.0..Oh. yeah. I'll give her a call.\Nsee if she wants to hang out.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:24.53.0:09:25.63.Default..0.0.0..Yeah.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:28.21.0:09:30.23.Default..0.0.0..What...\NDo they make out?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:30.30.0:09:31.31.Default..0.0.0..Better.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:31.38.0:09:33.08.Default..0.0.0..Comparable.\NComparable.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:33.15.0:09:39.59.Default..0.0.0..Whatever. It's over. I lost. I\Nguess you don't get a second chance.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:39.66.0:09:40.86.Default..0.0.0..I got a second chance.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:40.93.0:09:42.24.Default..0.0.0..What happened?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:42.31.0:09:43.58.Default..0.0.0..He came by my place tonight...
Dialogue: 0.0:09:45.35.0:09:48.03.Default..0.0.0..Simon.\NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:48.10.0:09:49.68.Default..0.0.0..I just feel like there's\Nsome unfinished business
Dialogue: 0.0:09:49.70.0:09:51.58.Default..0.0.0..between you and me.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:51.65.0:09:55.81.Default..0.0.0..Seeing you now has made me\Nrealize that breaking up with you
Dialogue: 0.0:09:55.87.0:09:58.17.Default..0.0.0..is the biggest mistake\NI made in my entire life.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:58.24.0:10:01.58.Default..0.0.0..Oh. I like where this is going.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:01.65.0:10:04.88.Default..0.0.0..I know this is crazy. and I'm\Nonly in town for a couple of days.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:04.90.0:10:07.38.Default..0.0.0..but do you want to go on a date?
Dialogue: 0.0:10:07.45.0:10:08.61.Default..0.0.0..He asked you out?
Dialogue: 0.0:10:08.64.0:10:11.10.Default..0.0.0..Oh. step into my web. Simon.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:11.17.0:10:12.29.Default..0.0.0..The coup de grace.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:12.36.0:10:13.61.Default..0.0.0..Finish him!
Dialogue: 0.0:10:15.33.0:10:17.21.Default..0.0.0..I'd love to!
Dialogue: 0.0:10:25.20.0:10:27.52.Default..0.0.0..Wait. You're going on\Na date with Simon?
Dialogue: 0.0:10:27.59.0:10:29.45.Default..0.0.0..That Simon?\NThe one we met?
Dialogue: 0.0:10:29.47.0:10:32.10.Default..0.0.0..Robin. this guy doesn't\Ndeserve a second chance.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:32.13.0:10:33.82.Default..0.0.0..Not after the way\Nhe treated you.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:33.85.0:10:36.93.Default..0.0.0..That was 10 years ago.\NPeople evolve.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:37.00.0:10:40.65.Default..0.0.0..I mean. are you the same person\Nthat you were in high school?
Dialogue: 0.0:10:40.72.0:10:42.72.Default..0.0.0..Oh. hell. no!
Dialogue: 0.0:10:42.79.0:10:44.30.Default..0.0.0..I think you're gonna enjoy this.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:44.37.0:10:45.72.Default..0.0.0..That my girl Michelle?
Dialogue: 0.0:10:45.79.0:10:47.17.Default..0.0.0..Bitch. you know it!
Dialogue: 0.0:10:47.24.0:10:48.48.Default..0.0.0..How she living?
Dialogue: 0.0:10:48.54.0:10:50.60.Default..0.0.0..She living the only way\Nshe know how to.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:50.63.0:10:52.33.Default..0.0.0..Large!\NOh. girl.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:52.40.0:10:54.53.Default..0.0.0..you gots to get\Nyour drink on up in here.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:54.60.0:10:57.41.Default..0.0.0..I'm hoping my fat ass can\Nhustle me up a vodka-Gatorade.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:57.44.0:10:58.79.Default..0.0.0..For reals!
Dialogue: 0.0:11:02.87.0:11:05.78.Default..0.0.0..I want her around all the time.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:05.84.0:11:10.31.Default..0.0.0..I'd even consider not trying to\Nsleep with her if that's what it takes.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:10.38.0:11:13.03.Default..0.0.0..Guys. I've decided\Nto seduce Michelle.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:20.91.0:11:21.92.Default..0.0.0..Yeah!
Dialogue: 0.0:11:21.99.0:11:24.86.Default..0.0.0..Guys. that was great.\NLet's take five.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:24.93.0:11:27.11.Default..0.0.0..Hey. babe. did you like it\Nafter my bass solo
Dialogue: 0.0:11:27.18.0:11:28.34.Default..0.0.0..when I flicked my pick at you?
Dialogue: 0.0:11:28.37.0:11:29.98.Default..0.0.0..That rocked.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:30.05.0:11:33.65.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. 'Cause I'm gonna\Nneed that pick back.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:33.72.0:11:36.01.Default..0.0.0..Oh. sure.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:36.07.0:11:37.65.Default..0.0.0..I think it's... It's cool.\NYou'll find it later.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:37.68.0:11:40.24.Default..0.0.0..Oh. cool. I wish I didn't have\Nto go to work in the morning.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:40.31.0:11:42.40.Default..0.0.0..Oh. but. babe.\Nyou got to go to work.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:42.46.0:11:44.31.Default..0.0.0..You got to play our\Ndemo on your show.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:44.33.0:11:47.15.Default..0.0.0..Oh. well. you know. it's\Nnot a show. It's the news.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:47.24.0:11:50.19.Default..0.0.0..Right. So you can be. like. "Hey.\Ndid you hear there's some news?
Dialogue: 0.0:11:50.26.0:11:52.50.Default..0.0.0.."There's this rad band\Nyou guys should check out."
Dialogue: 0.0:11:52.52.0:11:57.19.Default..0.0.0..And then play it. Just.\Nlike. the first three songs.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:57.26.0:12:02.32.Default..0.0.0..And now it's time for {\i1}Puppy Corner.{\i0}\Nsome little angels looking for a new home.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:02.38.0:12:04.67.Default..0.0.0..courtesy of the\NMidtown Animal Shelter.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:20.17.0:12:23.49.Default..0.0.0..Hey. a lot of puppies\Ngot adopted.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:23.55.0:12:25.03.Default..0.0.0..Of course. a lot of\Nthe people calling in
Dialogue: 0.0:12:25.06.0:12:27.22.Default..0.0.0..thought we were\Ngoing to kill them.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:27.24.0:12:30.69.Default..0.0.0..Robin. your revertigo is really\Nstarting to affect your work.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:30.76.0:12:31.91.Default..0.0.0..What's revertigo?
Dialogue: 0.0:12:31.98.0:12:33.81.Default..0.0.0..It's a stupid. made-up word\Nwith no meaning.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:33.88.0:12:35.58.Default..0.0.0..No. It's\Na phenomenon where.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:35.60.0:12:37.41.Default..0.0.0..when you're around people\Nfrom your past.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:37.44.0:12:39.11.Default..0.0.0..you start behaving like them.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:39.14.0:12:42.71.Default..0.0.0..Oh. One example\Nof that springs to mind.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:42.77.0:12:45.02.Default..0.0.0..I think we all know what it is.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:45.61.0:12:46.89.Default..0.0.0..We do?
Dialogue: 0.0:12:46.96.0:12:49.26.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. Ted.\NMe?
Dialogue: 0.0:12:49.33.0:12:51.73.Default..0.0.0..Whenever Ted's friend.\NPunchy. comes into town.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:51.80.0:12:54.57.Default..0.0.0..it's like. all of a sudden.\NTed's in high school again.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:54.64.0:12:58.67.Default..0.0.0..Okay. okay. First of all. his\Nname is Adam Punciarello.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:58.74.0:13:00.36.Default..0.0.0..and I don't do that.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:02.59.0:13:04.61.Default..0.0.0..Ooh!\NThat must be Adam.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:07.83.0:13:09.36.Default..0.0.0..'Sup. Punchy?\N'Sup. Shmosby?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:09.38.0:13:10.80.Default..0.0.0..You want to go?\NI'm already there!
Dialogue: 0.0:13:10.82.0:13:13.37.Default..0.0.0..Come on!\NThis is it!
Dialogue: 0.0:13:13.44.0:13:16.36.Default..0.0.0..Dude. seriously.\NI'm sorry about your dad.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:16.41.0:13:18.45.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. it was a real shock.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:19.48.0:13:21.81.Default..0.0.0..I can't believe you. of\Nall people. are saying this.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:21.83.0:13:23.08.Default..0.0.0..Why?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:23.15.0:13:24.78.Default..0.0.0..No reason.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:24.85.0:13:29.80.Default..0.0.0..Robin. the point is. what are\Nyou doing? I mean. this guy?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:29.87.0:13:32.29.Default..0.0.0..Okay. you want the truth?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:32.36.0:13:35.71.Default..0.0.0..I like Simon. I do.\NWe have fun together.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:35.78.0:13:39.31.Default..0.0.0..Oh. we know you do. honey.\Nbut we're worried about you.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:39.38.0:13:41.70.Default..0.0.0..You're worried?\NOkay. hold on.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:41.77.0:13:43.68.Default..0.0.0..Is there any version\Nof this conversation
Dialogue: 0.0:13:43.70.0:13:45.94.Default..0.0.0..where you guys don't sound\Nlike my parents?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:46.00.0:13:49.86.Default..0.0.0..I don't know. Is there any version\Nwhere you don't sound like a 16-year-old?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:49.92.0:13:52.35.Default..0.0.0..That's exactly what\Nmy mom would say.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:52.38.0:13:57.13.Default..0.0.0..No. If I was your mom. I would say.\N"We forbid you from seeing this boy."
Dialogue: 0.0:13:57.20.0:13:58.38.Default..0.0.0..Lily!
Dialogue: 0.0:13:58.45.0:14:00.37.Default..0.0.0..No. I'm sorry. but\Nit's for your own good.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:00.44.0:14:02.05.Default..0.0.0..This is my life!
Dialogue: 0.0:14:02.12.0:14:04.82.Default..0.0.0..You guys just don't get it!\NYou've never felt the way that I feel!
Dialogue: 0.0:14:04.84.0:14:07.94.Default..0.0.0..Now. now. We were once\Nyoung and in love. too.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:07.96.0:14:10.81.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. like. a billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:10.88.0:14:13.58.Default..0.0.0..You've been drinking.\Nhaven't you?
Dialogue: 0.0:14:13.63.0:14:16.51.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. we all have. You\Nbought the last round.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:16.53.0:14:17.94.Default..0.0.0..You're not going to\Nthat show tonight!
Dialogue: 0.0:14:17.97.0:14:20.04.Default..0.0.0..Oh. yes. I am.\Nand you know what else?
Dialogue: 0.0:14:20.10.0:14:23.12.Default..0.0.0..Tonight. after the show. Simon\Nand I are going all the way!
Dialogue: 0.0:14:23.19.0:14:26.13.Default..0.0.0..Young lady.\Nget back here!
Dialogue: 0.0:14:26.98.0:14:28.28.Default..0.0.0..Thanks for your help.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:30.03.0:14:31.29.Default..0.0.0..Hey. so. today at work...
Dialogue: 0.0:14:31.32.0:14:32.77.Default..0.0.0..Not now. Ted!
Dialogue: 0.0:14:39.82.0:14:42.43.Default..0.0.0..Hey. Simon.\NGreat show.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:42.49.0:14:43.93.Default..0.0.0..You guys still rock.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:44.00.0:14:47.76.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. Totally\Ndug my bass solo.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:47.83.0:14:51.50.Default..0.0.0..Man! Why can't I\Nalways feel this alive?
Dialogue: 0.0:14:52.94.0:14:56.56.Default..0.0.0..God. I just love\Nseeing you so happy.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:56.62.0:15:00.59.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. about that.\NListen. babe.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:01.78.0:15:02.95.Default..0.0.0..It's over.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:03.01.0:15:04.15.Default..0.0.0..What?
Dialogue: 0.0:15:04.22.0:15:06.78.Default..0.0.0..I'm getting back together\Nwith Louise Marsh.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:06.85.0:15:09.52.Default..0.0.0..What?\NYou're kidding me.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:11.34.0:15:13.96.Default..0.0.0..You're breaking up\Nwith me? Again?
Dialogue: 0.0:15:14.03.0:15:17.73.Default..0.0.0..For the same ex-girlfriend?\NIn the same van?
Dialogue: 0.0:15:17.80.0:15:22.25.Default..0.0.0..What is it? Her parents got a\Npool? Is that still the reason?
Dialogue: 0.0:15:22.32.0:15:26.12.Default..0.0.0..Well. her folks\Ndid just put in a Jacuzz.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:32.49.0:15:34.74.Default..0.0.0..I'm sorry. Robin.\NI'm fine. really.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:34.81.0:15:37.01.Default..0.0.0..Oh. Robin. I'm gonna\Ntell you for reals.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:37.08.0:15:39.32.Default..0.0.0..Simon's a dog.\NYou feel me. Chelle?
Dialogue: 0.0:15:39.38.0:15:43.02.Default..0.0.0..Mmm-hmm. For reals. He a scrub.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:43.09.0:15:44.39.Default..0.0.0..True that.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:44.46.0:15:47.74.Default..0.0.0..I'm gonna get me my\Nchampagne and grape soda on.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:49.13.0:15:50.64.Default..0.0.0..So. how's Columbia?
Dialogue: 0.0:15:50.71.0:15:51.73.Default..0.0.0..Great!
Dialogue: 0.0:15:51.80.0:15:54.01.Default..0.0.0..I'm almost done\Nwith my dissertation.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:54.08.0:15:57.93.Default..0.0.0..I'm getting a Ph.D.\Nin behavioral psychology.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:58.00.0:15:59.38.Default..0.0.0..Can I make an observation?
Dialogue: 0.0:15:59.40.0:16:00.97.Default..0.0.0..Oh. I know.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:01.04.0:16:04.17.Default..0.0.0..Whenever I'm around Lily. she\Njust brings out that side of me.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:04.24.0:16:06.07.Default..0.0.0..There's a psychological term\Nfor the phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:06.09.0:16:07.59.Default..0.0.0..Revertigo?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:07.61.0:16:09.32.Default..0.0.0..Actually. it's\Nassociative regression.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:09.35.0:16:11.41.Default..0.0.0..You see. the neural\Npathways that...
Dialogue: 0.0:16:12.75.0:16:16.84.Default..0.0.0..Oh. no. you did not\Njust put on my jam!
Dialogue: 0.0:16:16.90.0:16:18.69.Default..0.0.0..Put your hands up. girl!
Dialogue: 0.0:16:18.76.0:16:20.97.Default..0.0.0..Holla!\NHolla!
Dialogue: 0.0:16:22.56.0:16:24.99.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}One by one.\Nwe all had to go home.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:16:27.83.0:16:29.80.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}Soon. it was just Robin.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:16:38.28.0:16:42.41.Default..0.0.0..All right. I can't find your\Nvideo. I've wasted three days...
Dialogue: 0.0:16:44.47.0:16:45.95.Default..0.0.0..What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0.0:16:46.02.0:16:47.55.Default..0.0.0..Uh...
Dialogue: 0.0:16:49.25.0:16:54.12.Default..0.0.0..Simon dumped me in his van\Nafter the show.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:54.19.0:16:57.18.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. Robin. that was.\Nlike. 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:57.25.0:16:58.33.Default..0.0.0..No. tonight.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:58.40.0:17:00.35.Default..0.0.0..Ooh! Really?
Dialogue: 0.0:17:02.07.0:17:05.49.Default..0.0.0..Oh! Oh. come here.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:07.64.0:17:09.14.Default..0.0.0..Come here.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:11.44.0:17:14.31.Default..0.0.0..It's just...\NWhen I was young.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:14.38.0:17:19.62.Default..0.0.0..I was so vulnerable and\Nopen to things. you know?
Dialogue: 0.0:17:19.68.0:17:24.25.Default..0.0.0..And I guess I just... I\Nwanted to feel that way again.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:26.11.0:17:28.31.Default..0.0.0..I wanted to be 16 again.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:29.21.0:17:31.89.Default..0.0.0..Robin. that is\Nthe stupidest thing
Dialogue: 0.0:17:31.96.0:17:34.08.Default..0.0.0..I've ever heard\Ncome out of your mouth.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:34.15.0:17:36.28.Default..0.0.0..You want to be 16 again?
Dialogue: 0.0:17:36.35.0:17:39.92.Default..0.0.0..I have watched your first Robin\NSparkles video 1.000 times.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:39.99.0:17:42.54.Default..0.0.0..and it's not because I'm\Nproud of you as a friend.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:42.61.0:17:45.54.Default..0.0.0..It's because you were\Ntotally. totally lame back then.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:46.84.0:17:49.03.Default..0.0.0..But now. come on.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:49.10.0:17:51.70.Default..0.0.0..You're the most awesome\Nperson I have ever known.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:51.77.0:17:53.43.Default..0.0.0..Well. second most awesome.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:53.50.0:17:56.17.Default..0.0.0..Right. Of course.\Nthe first being you.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:56.24.0:18:01.32.Default..0.0.0..No. No. The first is this guy who\Nlives in a place called the mirror.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:01.39.0:18:04.29.Default..0.0.0..What up?
Dialogue: 0.0:18:04.36.0:18:08.18.Default..0.0.0..I'm saying that you are\Nway more awesome
Dialogue: 0.0:18:08.25.0:18:10.23.Default..0.0.0..than Simon ever will be.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:14.34.0:18:17.37.Default..0.0.0..Barney. do you want to\Ncome back to my place?
Dialogue: 0.0:18:17.44.0:18:18.82.Default..0.0.0..Your place?
Dialogue: 0.0:18:28.37.0:18:32.05.Default..0.0.0..Are you sure you want\Nto do this? Yeah. I am.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:32.12.0:18:33.62.Default..0.0.0..Let's just not tell anyone\Nabout this. okay?
Dialogue: 0.0:18:33.64.0:18:34.96.Default..0.0.0..Of course.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:37.76.0:18:39.86.Default..0.0.0..So. should I just put it in?
Dialogue: 0.0:18:40.82.0:18:42.30.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. why not?
Dialogue: 0.0:18:56.38.0:18:59.87.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Met you at the mall{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:18:59.93.0:19:04.15.Default..0.0.0..This was my big artistic\Nfollow-up to {\i1}Let's Go to the Mall.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:05.52.0:19:07.59.Default..0.0.0..It kind of tanked.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:07.66.0:19:11.44.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ My friends said\NI was a fool{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:11.51.0:19:13.25.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ You're a fool\N♪ Shut up{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:13.31.0:19:14.51.Default..0.0.0..Is that Tiffany?
Dialogue: 0.0:19:14.58.0:19:16.15.Default..0.0.0..Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:16.22.0:19:18.01.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ 'Cause you were older\Nand got kicked out of school{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:18.04.0:19:19.64.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ You are so rad{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:19.70.0:19:24.54.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Together we were\Ngonna travel the globe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:24.61.0:19:29.51.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ From Alberta to Ontario{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:30.83.0:19:33.28.Default..0.0.0..It's everything I want\Nit to be and more.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:33.30.0:19:34.67.Default..0.0.0..Oh. I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:34.74.0:19:38.15.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ And now I'm building\Nsandcastles in the sand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:38.22.0:19:40.72.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Sandcastles in the sand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:40.79.0:19:44.83.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Thought I could fly\Nwhen you held my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:44.90.0:19:46.88.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Thought I could fly\N♪ But now{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:46.95.0:19:51.58.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Eternity returns\Nto black and white{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:51.65.0:19:53.42.Default..0.0.0..Is that Alan Thicke?
Dialogue: 0.0:19:53.49.0:19:55.00.Default..0.0.0..Yeah.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:55.07.0:19:59.09.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ It was the greatest week\Nand a half of my life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:19:59.16.0:20:02.49.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ We used to\Ngo to the beach{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:02.56.0:20:04.46.Default..0.0.0..You know. if you re-edit it.\Nthere's a tampon commercial
Dialogue: 0.0:20:04.48.0:20:06.65.Default..0.0.0..in here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:06.72.0:20:12.19.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ On our favorite bench{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:12.26.0:20:17.83.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ We'd sit and talk\Nand you taught me to French{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:20.25.0:20:22.39.Default..0.0.0..Do you see how lame\Nyou were back then?
Dialogue: 0.0:20:22.42.0:20:24.58.Default..0.0.0..Yeah. you're right.\NI was lame.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:24.65.0:20:25.76.Default..0.0.0..Totally lame.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:25.79.0:20:28.17.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ ...so unfair{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:28.24.0:20:31.34.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ You don't understand\Nour love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:31.41.0:20:33.35.Default..0.0.0..And. of course. the robot\Nmakes an appearance
Dialogue: 0.0:20:33.38.0:20:35.13.Default..0.0.0..in the sad love ballad.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:35.20.0:20:37.40.Default..0.0.0..He was my sidekick.\NHe had to be.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:37.46.0:20:38.86.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}And so they watched it again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:38.88.0:20:44.55.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Come back. please\NI've changed my mind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:44.62.0:20:48.87.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Let's go all the way{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:48.94.0:20:50.28.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ I'm ready{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:50.34.0:20:51.74.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Let's do it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:55.02.0:20:56.77.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ I miss you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:56.83.0:20:57.93.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}And again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:20:57.95.0:21:00.72.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ Sandcastles may be cute{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:21:00.79.0:21:02.82.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ I'm on the pill now{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:21:02.89.0:21:04.27.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}And again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:21:04.34.0:21:06.61.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ But now all they do\Nis remind me of you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:21:06.68.0:21:10.18.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}They watched it\Nover and over that night until finally.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:21:10.25.0:21:11.75.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}they stopped watching.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0.0:21:12.78.0:21:14.85.Default..0.0.0..{\i1}♪ You said it'd be okay ♪{\i0}
